{"questionId":"11775","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Adesh wants to model the cooling of a metal rod. He heats the rod and records its temperature as it cools.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/dc3df2bca8961d737b21e2d9332e61c01d58dcad.png\"></p>\n<p>He believes the temperature can be modeled by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T\\left( t \\right) = a{{\\text{e}}^{bt}} + 25\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>25</mn>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Hence</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>predict the temperature of the metal rod after 3 minutes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T\\left( {180} \\right) = 49.1{e^{ - 0.00870\\left( {180} \\right)}} + 25 = 35.2\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>180</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>49.1</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>0.00870</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>180</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>25</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>35.2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11775","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.15c.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"predict the temperature of the metal rod after 3 minutes.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}